The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Mali open to shorter 2011 World Cup

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

Chennai: The acting president of the International Cricket Council (ICC), South African Ray Mali, is open to the idea of the next World Cup being staged over a lesser number of days. 

That could be looked into, yes, Mali told The Telegraph on Saturday afternoon. 

The last World Cup began on March 13 and ended on April 28. The next will be held in the subcontinent, in 2011. 

Mali, meanwhile, said hes ready to provide visionary leadership over the next 12 months. Compatriot Percy Sonns death has given him the chair. 

Cricket is alive and kicking and can compete with the Bollywoods of this world, he insisted and said that the Twenty20 concept be allowed a run. 




